videos.headline: Cozart takes it up the middle for a Boise TD
videos.description: Montell Cozart opens the scoring for Boise State with a 28 yard touchdown run. Boise State lead 7-0.

videos.headline: Owens scores for UNM on 4th down
videos.description: Tyrone Owens takes a pitch from Lamar Jordan on 4th and 1 for the New Mexico touchdown to tie the game 7-7.

videos.headline: Cozart connects with Wilson for a big 47 yards
videos.description: Montell Cozart finds Cedrick Wilson over the middle for 47 yards on a great catch for Boise State.

videos.headline: Roh gets open in end zone for a Boise TD
videos.description: Jake Roh finds some space in the corner of the end zone on a pass from Montell Cozart to give Boise State a 14-7 lead.

videos.headline: UNM QB knocked out on late targeting hit by Boise State
videos.description: Jordan Lamar takes a late hit from Chase Hatada and has to leave the game. Hatada is ejected from the game for targeting.

videos.headline: UNM's Davie: Gameplan doesn't change under Gerhart
videos.description: New Mexico coach Bob Davie doesn't think his gameplan will change after Lamar Jordan had to be replaced by Coltin Gerhart.

videos.headline: BSU's Harsin: Cozart operating well in the first half
videos.description: Boise State head coach Bryan Harsin liked what he saw from quarterback Montell Cozart in the first half.

videos.headline: Boise TE scores wildcat TD
videos.description: Boise State TE Jake Roh takes the direct snap and scores a rushing touchdown to increase the lead to 21-7.

videos.headline: Gerhart finds Umeh for a late UNM TD
videos.description: Coltin Gerhart throws a contested 14-yard touchdown to Anselem Umeh late in the 4th quarter.

videos.headline: BSU's Harsin on Cozart: He was fantastic
videos.description: Boise State head coach Bryan Harsin was impressed by his quarterback Montell Cozart's preparation against UNM.

videos.headline: Boise State learned from last week's loss
videos.description: Dave Flemming and Brock Huard compare Boise State's devastating loss last week to Washington State to tonight's win against New Mexico.
